ss="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card__read-more"> Read More </button></div></div><div class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-card-toolbar mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card__toolbar"><div class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-card-toolbar__buttons"><button class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-helpful-button" data-feedback-id="4818e356996b1f2864c097c60a326618298473f2_6649624" data-click-tracked="false" helpfulbtneventaction=""><svg class="ugc-shared-icon-helpful-fill"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#ugc-shared-icon-helpful-fill"></use></svg><svg class="ugc-shared-icon-helpful-outline"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#ugc-shared-icon-helpful-outline"></use></svg> 701</button><button class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-response-button" data-click-tracked="false"><svg class="ugc-shared-icon-reply"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#ugc-shared-icon-reply"></use></svg> Reply</button><!--v-if--></div><!--v-if--></div></div></div><!--v-if--></div><div data-feedback-id="23b3ad92c1f7693683f6d5305d223b0252de9253_6649624" data-response-count="0" class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card--review mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card--review-23b3ad92c1f7693683f6d5305d223b0252de9253_6649624 mm-recipes-ugc-threaded-carousel__card"><div class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card__content"><!--v-if--><!--v-if--><div class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-card-byline"><!-- Don't show user avatar in read only mode --><span class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-card-byline__avatar-wrapper"><svg class="ugc-shared-icon-avatar-2 ugc-threaded-icon-avatar-2 mm-recipes-ugc-shared-card-byline__avatar-icon"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#ugc-shared-icon-avatar-2"></use></svg></span><span class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-card-byline__username"><!--v-if--><span class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-card-byline__username-text">SPORTSNUT</span><!--v-if--></span><!--v-if--></div><div class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-card-meta"><!-- Feedback Star Rating --><div class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-star-rating"><span class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-star-rating__star"><svg class="ugc-shared-icon-star mm-recipes-ugc-shared-star-rating__icon"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#ugc-shared-icon-star"></use></svg></span><span class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-star-rating__star"><svg class="ugc-shared-icon-star mm-recipes-ugc-shared-star-rating__icon"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#ugc-shared-icon-star"></use></svg></span><span class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-star-rating__star"><svg class="ugc-shared-icon-star mm-recipes-ugc-shared-star-rating__icon"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#ugc-shared-icon-star"></use></svg></span><span class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-star-rating__star"><svg class="ugc-shared-icon-star mm-recipes-ugc-shared-star-rating__icon"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#ugc-shared-icon-star"></use></svg></span><span class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-star-rating__star"><svg class="ugc-shared-icon-star mm-recipes-ugc-shared-star-rating__icon"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#ugc-shared-icon-star"></use></svg></span></div><!-- Feedback Publish Date --><span class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-card-meta__date">01/05/2006</span></div><!--v-if--><div class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card__body-container"><div class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card__body mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card__body--show-read-more-expanded"><!--v-if--><div class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card__text-wrapper"><div class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card__text">These chocolate chip cookies were very, very good. I have been trying chocolate chip cookie recipes forever to find the perfect cookie and this one is very close. They weren't too cake-like and they weren't thin and greasy, they were the perfect in-between cookie. That said, the dough is very thick once you mix all the ingredients together. A bit of advice - if you like a thinner cookie and not so cake-like, make a smaller ball of dough and when you place it on the cookie sheet be sure to flatten it quite a bit as the dough doesn't seem to spread when in the oven. If you like thick cookies, just leave them in the ball and they'll stay big. As the recipe states, they are crisp on the outside and chewy on the inside - still nice and moist the following day. I added some Skor toffee bits to the recipe and they turned out amazing - will definitely make again!! Thanks for sharing. <!--v-if--></div><button data-click-tracked="false" class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card__read-more"> Read More </button></div></div><div class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-card-toolbar mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card__toolbar"><div class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-card-toolbar__buttons"><button class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-helpful-button" data-feedback-id="23b3ad92c1f7693683f6d5305d223b0252de9253_6649624" data-click-tracked="false" helpfulbtneventaction=""><svg class="ugc-shared-icon-helpful-fill"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#ugc-shared-icon-helpful-fill"></use></svg><svg class="ugc-shared-icon-helpful-outline"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#ugc-shared-icon-helpful-outline"></use></svg> 543</button><button class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-response-button" data-click-tracked="false"><svg class="ugc-shared-icon-reply"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#ugc-shared-icon-reply"></use></svg> Reply</button><!--v-if--></div><!--v-if--></div></div></div><!--v-if--></div><div data-feedback-id="97bbcf612b88f451460d3554860e81747dd2bdee_6649624" data-response-count="0" class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card--review mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card--review-97bbcf612b88f451460d3554860e81747dd2bdee_6649624 mm-recipes-ugc-threaded-carousel__card"><div class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card__content"><!--v-if--><!--v-if--><div class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-card-byline"><!-- Don't show user avatar in read only mode --><span class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-card-byline__avatar-wrapper"><svg class="ugc-shared-icon-avatar-1 ugc-threaded-icon-avatar-1 mm-recipes-ugc-shared-card-byline__avatar-icon"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#ugc-shared-icon-avatar-1"></use></svg></span><span class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-card-byline__username"><!--v-if--><span class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-card-byline__username-text">MommyFromSeattle</span><!--v-if--></span><!--v-if--></div><div class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-card-meta"><!-- Feedback Star Rating --><div class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-star-rating"><span class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-star-rating__star"><svg class="ugc-shared-icon-star mm-recipes-ugc-shared-star-rating__icon"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#ugc-shared-icon-star"></use></svg></span><span class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-star-rating__star"><svg class="ugc-shared-icon-star mm-recipes-ugc-shared-star-rating__icon"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#ugc-shared-icon-star"></use></svg></span><span class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-star-rating__star"><svg class="ugc-shared-icon-star mm-recipes-ugc-shared-star-rating__icon"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#ugc-shared-icon-star"></use></svg></span><span class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-star-rating__star"><svg class="ugc-shared-icon-star mm-recipes-ugc-shared-star-rating__icon"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#ugc-shared-icon-star"></use></svg></span><span class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-star-rating__star"><svg class="ugc-shared-icon-star-outline mm-recipes-ugc-shared-star-rating__icon"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#ugc-shared-icon-star-outline"></use></svg></span></div><!-- Feedback Publish Date --><span class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-card-meta__date">02/05/2008</span></div><!--v-if--><div class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card__body-container"><div class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card__body mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card__body--show-read-more"><!--v-if--><div class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card__text-wrapper"><div class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card__text">Superb. I give 4 1/2 stars to the original recipe since it calls for 50/50 white &amp; brown sugar. Since then, I've used ALL brown sugar and increased the salt to 2/3 teaspoons, and it was PERFECT. The flavor was a lot richer. I've tried 4 recipes from this site and I'm glad I finally found my Master recipe. Some of the other recipes on this site calls for pudding mix in the batter - which baffles me. This is an excellent cookie (soft and chewy) that has only good old-fashioned ingredients. Most importantly, it stays chewy, not hard. Look no further folks, this is the one. (For walnut sized dough balls, and I did roll them for a more uniform look, 11-12 min. was perfect. 10 min. was still a little doughy). TIP - if your cookies sit around for a few days (if that's possible) and gets a little dry, put a fresh slice of sandwich bread in the same container as the cookies and they will moisten right up. <!--v-if--></div><button data-click-tracked="false" class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card__read-more"> Read More </button></div></div><div class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-card-toolbar mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card__toolbar"><div class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-card-toolbar__buttons"><button class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-helpful-button" data-feedback-id="97bbcf612b88f451460d3554860e81747dd2bdee_6649624" data-click-tracked="false" helpfulbtneventaction=""><svg class="ugc-shared-icon-helpful-fill"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#ugc-shared-icon-helpful-fill"></use></svg><svg class="ugc-shared-icon-helpful-outline"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#ugc-shared-icon-helpful-outline"></use></svg> 428</button><button class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-response-button" data-click-tracked="false"><svg class="ugc-shared-icon-reply"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#ugc-shared-icon-reply"></use></svg> Reply</button><!--v-if--></div><!--v-if--></div></div></div><!--v-if--></div><div data-feedback-id="3e6b6f379d33c7142f874ce72e21caeef582cffb_6649624" data-response-count="0" class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card--review mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card--review-3e6b6f379d33c7142f874ce72e21caeef582cffb_6649624 mm-recipes-ugc-threaded-carousel__card"><div class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card__content"><!--v-if--><!--v-if--><div class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-card-byline"><!-- Don't show user avatar in read only mode --><span class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-card-byline__avatar-wrapper"><svg class="ugc-shared-icon-avatar-2 ugc-threaded-icon-avatar-2 mm-recipes-ugc-shared-card-byline__avatar-icon"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#ugc-shared-icon-avatar-2"></use></svg></span><span class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-card-byline__username"><!--v-if--><span class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-card-byline__username-text">cxgc5b24fd</span><!--v-if--></span><!--v-if--></div><div class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-card-meta"><!-- Feedback Star Rating --><div class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-star-rating"><span class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-star-rating__star"><svg class="ugc-shared-icon-star mm-recipes-ugc-shared-star-rating__icon"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#ugc-shared-icon-star"></use></svg></span><span class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-star-rating__star"><svg class="ugc-shared-icon-star mm-recipes-ugc-shared-star-rating__icon"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#ugc-shared-icon-star"></use></svg></span><span class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-star-rating__star"><svg class="ugc-shared-icon-star mm-recipes-ugc-shared-star-rating__icon"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#ugc-shared-icon-star"></use></svg></span><span class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-star-rating__star"><svg clas