.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#ugc-shared-icon-star"></use></svg></span><span class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-star-rating__star"><svg class="ugc-shared-icon-star mm-recipes-ugc-shared-star-rating__icon"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#ugc-shared-icon-star"></use></svg></span></div><!-- Feedback Publish Date --><span class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-card-meta__date">08/24/2018</span></div><!--v-if--><div class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card__body-container"><div class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card__body mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card__body--show-read-more"><!--v-if--><div class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card__text-wrapper"><div class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card__text">This cookie was amazing! They baked perfectly in my oven at 325 for 12 minutes. I followed a couple suggestions of reducing white sugar to 1/2 C and increasing brown sugar to 1 1/2 C as well as adding 1 C of white chocolate chips. Instead of walnuts I added roasted pecan pieces to mine. My husband took one bite and said "you're a goddess" haha This will be my go-to cookie recipe <!--v-if--></div><button data-click-tracked="false" class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card__read-more"> Read More </button></div></div><div class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-card-toolbar mm-recipes-ugc-shared-item-card__toolbar"><div class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-card-toolbar__buttons"><button class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-helpful-button" data-feedback-id="05dffefeacdc91b2d4b4f722f3124bed4aba835b_6649624" data-click-tracked="false" helpfulbtneventaction=""><svg class="ugc-shared-icon-helpful-fill"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#ugc-shared-icon-helpful-fill"></use></svg><svg class="ugc-shared-icon-helpful-outline"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#ugc-shared-icon-helpful-outline"></use></svg> 16</button><button class="mm-recipes-ugc-shared-response-button" data-click-tracked="false"><svg class="ugc-shared-icon-reply"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w